- **Childhood → Ron**: Added "What finally ended the lean years was a role built to be everything he is not. His relationship to it is the next tell." Carries the "lean years" keyword forward and frames Ron as the inversion before the section makes that case.
- **Last of Us → Mullally**: Added "Offerman did not have to imagine a love that reorganizes a life. He has lived inside one for over twenty years." Carries Bill-and-Frank's love-story thread directly into Offerman's real marriage (and pre-echoes the section's own "a love that reorganizes a whole life" line).
- **Mullally → Workbench**: Added "The marriage was not the first place Offerman went looking for that kind of calm." Bridges marriage-sanctuary to workbench-sanctuary on the "calm" keyword without re-firing the overused "separate/wanting self" motif.

